sentence shows that quoque is indispens- able. The writer might have said ⁴ inci- dunt enim causae in quibus haee scientia requiritur,’ and the reference of haec to the three last-named arts would have been more obvious. But he chose to vary the sentence by inserting the paratactic but logically subordinate clause ‘plurimae quidem . . . desideratur,’ with which ‘ incidunt' is less appropriate: quoque is then needed for emphasis. John points out also the appropriateness of quibus . . . desideratur, of the indispensable‚ as against in quibus . . . requiritur of what is less frequently called into play.—For kaec- scientiae-harum artium scientia, cp. ⁴ ei scientiae‚’ Cic. de Or. i. §10 for ‘eius artis scientiae' (mathematies): ‘istam scientiam (of jurisprudence) ib. 5 248: sine ea scientia quam dixi, Or. ξ 118.
